text: Osmavandan (, also Romanized as ‘Os̄māvandān; also known as Usmamanda) is a small village in the Central District of Shaft County, in Gilan, in Iran. During the 2006 census, the number of people living there was 759. These people were divided into 216 families. == References == Category:Pages with unreviewed translations Category:Villages in Iran Category:Gilan Province
